00:39:58.190 --> 00:40:01.280
Is that something that you
think about in your research,

00:40:01.280 --> 00:40:06.910 position:56%
how people have also subverted these
technologies using perhaps less

00:40:06.910 --> 00:40:11.440
sophisticated or more
nave modes of technology?

00:40:11.440 --> 00:40:14.390
&gt;&gt; Ivan Chaar-Lopez:
So the ADITS system,

00:40:14.390 --> 00:40:17.840
as I mentioned, produced a card.

00:40:17.840 --> 00:40:21.030
The goal was every alien resident

00:40:21.030 --> 00:40:23.920
in the United States would
have this card as a mode

00:40:23.920 --> 00:40:26.450
of identifying his or herself.

00:40:26.450 --> 00:40:33.840 position:56%
And that came about because the
original green card as it was called

00:40:33.840 --> 00:40:36.320
that was actually used
since the 1940's,

00:40:36.320 --> 00:40:39.040 position:56%
there were different versions of it.

00:40:39.040 --> 00:40:42.320
So there was no standard
version of a green card.

00:40:42.320 --> 00:40:45.670
So they wanted to create
finally a standard version of it,

00:40:45.670 --> 00:40:50.790
because a lot of migrants
crossing the border --

00:40:50.790 --> 00:40:52.090
not through the checkpoints,

00:40:52.090 --> 00:40:54.930
but even also through the
checkpoints themselves.

00:40:54.930 --> 00:40:59.580
They carried what the
